    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Terminology",
        "content": "- **Still Water**: Water without any flow.\n- **Stream/Current**: The flow of water.\n- **Downstream**: Boat and stream moving in the same direction.\n- **Upstream**: Boat and stream moving in opposite directions."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "topic": "Basic Formulas",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Speed Relationships",
        "content": "- Speed downstream = Speed of boat + Speed of stream\n- Speed upstream = Speed of boat − Speed of stream\n\n**Example:**\nBoat speed = 10 km/hr, Stream speed = 2 km/hr\nDownstream = 10 + 2 = 12 km/hr\nUpstream = 10 − 2 = 8 km/hr"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "topic": "Finding Boat and Stream Speed",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Using Upstream & Downstream",
        "content": "- Speed of boat = (Downstream + Upstream)/2\n- Speed of stream = (Downstream − Upstream)/2\n\n**Example:**\nDownstream = 14 km/hr, Upstream = 6 km/hr\nBoat = (14 + 6)/2 = 10 km/hr\nStream = (14 − 6)/2 = 4 km/hr"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "topic": "Practice Example 1",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Basic Calculation",
        "content": "**Q:** A boat can go 30 km downstream in 3 hours and return in 5 hours. Find speed of boat and stream.\n**Solution:**\nDownstream speed = 30/3 = 10 km/hr\nUpstream speed = 30/5 = 6 km/hr\nBoat speed = (10+6)/2 = 8 km/hr\nStream speed = (10−6)/2 = 2 km/hr"
      }
    ]
